    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.13) leading the charge as our strongest play. While his eighth-order slot usually suppresses value, the combination of a favorable matchup against Meibrys Kelly, significant wind-out conditions, and elite potential for a stolen base against a pitcher with a slow delivery makes him our high-ceiling target for speed. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (75.14) provides high-end utility production; batting second against Tyler Mahle, he benefits from a strong park factor and a projection buoyed by his recent form and a favorable SP skill matchup. **Trea Turner** (68.00) and **Colt Keith** (66.91) remain essential starts, with the latter expected to exploit a high-efficiency spot against Jack Leiter, whose slow delivery provides the specific edge we covet for our stolen base-heavy strategy.\n\nThe decision to bench **Jerar Encarnacion** (41.97) was our most narrow margin today. While he possesses the requisite power profile, his matchup against Steven Matz offered a lower cumulative efficiency score than our active outfielders, and his placement in the bottom third of the order significantly capped his run-scoring probability. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Dillon Dingler** (46.82) and **Josh Smith** (40.29), both of whom are operating under \"Lineup Pending\" designations; should these players be shifted out of their projected spots or benched by their managers, their utility will drop below our acceptable threshold. Additionally, while **Yordan Alvarez** (63.71) remains a core piece, his score is slightly tempered today due to an L/L platoon disadvantage against Suarez. We are monitoring **Christian Yelich** and **Zac Veen**, who remain sidelined on the IL and in the minors, respectively, leaving our depth options like **Luke Raley** and **Lars Nootbaar** on high alert should late-breaking lineup changes occur.",
